{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2784a"},"text":"§ 2784a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Management of travel cards","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Disbursement of Travel Allowances Directly to Creditors","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Defense shall require that any part of a travel or transportation allowance of an employee of the Department of Defense or a member of the armed forces be disbursed directly to the issuer of a Defense travel card if the amount is disbursed to the issuer in payment of amounts of expenses of official travel that are charged by the employee or member on the Defense travel card.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Defense may waive the requirement for a direct payment to a travel card issuer under paragraph (1) in any case the Secretary determines appropriate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For the purposes of this subsection, the travel and transportation allowances referred to in paragraph (1) are amounts to which an employee of the Department of Defense is entitled under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5702"},"text":"section 5702 of title 5","children":[],"tail":" or a member of the armed forces is entitled under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s452"},"text":"section 452 of title 37","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Offsets for Delinquent Travel Card Charges","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Defense may require that there be deducted and withheld from any basic pay payable to an employee of the Department of Defense or a member of the armed forces any amount that is owed by the employee or member to a creditor by reason of one or more charges of expenses of official travel of the employee or member on a Defense travel card issued by the creditor if the employee or member—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is delinquent in the payment of such amount under the terms of the contract under which the card is issued; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3a9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" does not dispute the amount of the delinquency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3aa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amount deducted and withheld from pay under paragraph (1) with respect to a debt owed a creditor as described in that paragraph shall be disbursed to the creditor to reduce the amount of the debt.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3ab-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The amount of pay deducted and withheld from the pay owed to an employee or member with respect to a pay period under paragraph (1) may not exceed 15 percent of the disposable pay of the employee or member for that pay period, except that a higher amount may be deducted and withheld with the written consent of the employee or member.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3ac-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Defense shall prescribe procedures for deducting and withholding amounts from pay under this subsection. The procedures shall be substantially equivalent to the procedures under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s3716"},"text":"section 3716 of title 31","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3ad-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Offsets of Retired Pay","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of a former employee of the Department of Defense or a retired member of the armed forces who is receiving retired pay and who owes an amount to a creditor by reason of one or more charges on a Defense travel card that were made before the retirement of the employee or member, the Secretary may require amounts to be deducted and withheld from any retired pay of the former employee or retired member in the same manner and subject to the same conditions as the Secretary deducts and withholds amounts from basic pay payable to an employee or member under subsection (b).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3ae-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Determinations of Creditworthiness for Issuance of Defense Travel Card","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3af-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Defense shall evaluate the creditworthiness of an employee of the Department of Defense or a member of armed forces before issuing a Defense travel card to such an employee or member. The evaluation may include an examination of the individual’s credit history in available credit records.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An individual may not be issued a Defense travel card if the individual is found not creditworthy as a result of the evaluation required under paragraph (1).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Regulations on Disciplinary Action","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Defense shall prescribe regulations for making determinations regarding the taking of disciplinary action, including assessment of penalties, against Department of Defense personnel for improper, fraudulent, or abusive use of Defense travel cards by such personnel.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The regulations prescribed under paragraph (1) shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/e/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provide for appropriate adverse personnel actions or other punishment to be imposed in cases in which employees of the Department of Defense violate such regulations or are negligent or engage in misuse, abuse, or fraud with respect to a Defense travel card, including removal in appropriate cases; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/e/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provide that a violation of such regulations by a person subject to chapter 47 of this title (the Uniform Code of Military Justice) is punishable as a violation of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s892"},"text":"section 892 of this title","children":[],"tail":" (article 92 of the Uniform Code of Military Justice)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/f/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Defense travel card” means a charge or credit card that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/f/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is issued to an employee of the Department of Defense or a member of the armed forces under a contract entered into by the Department of Defense with the issuer of the card; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3b9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/f/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is to be used for charging expenses incurred by the employee or member in connection with official travel.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3ba-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/f/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “disposable pay”, with respect to a pay period, means the amount equal to the excess of the amount of basic pay or retired pay, as the case may be, payable for the pay period over the total of the amounts deducted and withheld from such pay.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3bb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/f/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “retired pay” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3bc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/f/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of a former employee of the Department of Defense, any retirement benefit payable to that individual, out of the Civil Service Retirement and Disability Fund, based (in whole or in part) on service performed by such individual as a civilian employee of the Department of Defense; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3bd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/f/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in the case of a retired member of the armed forces or member of the Fleet Reserve or Fleet Marine Corps Reserve, retired or retainer pay to which the member is entitled.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3be-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2784a/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Exclusion of Coast Guard","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"This section does not apply to the Coast Guard.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida9d0f3bf-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/314/dA/tX/s1008/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–314, div. A, title X, § 1008(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-02"},"text":"Dec. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2634"},"text":"116 Stat. 2634","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/dA/tX/s1009/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, div. A, title X, § 1009(a)","children":[],"tail":"–(c)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-11-24"},"text":"Nov. 24, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1587"},"text":"117 Stat. 1587","children":[],"tail":", 1588; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/364/dA/tX/s1071/a/25"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–364, div. A, title X, § 1071(a)(25)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2399"},"text":"120 Stat. 2399","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/81/dA/tVI/s631/f/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–81, div. A, title VI, § 631(f)(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/1465"},"text":"125 Stat. 1465","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/dA/tX/s1076/a/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, div. A, title X, § 1076(a)(9)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1948"},"text":"126 Stat. 1948","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81/dA/tVI/s603/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title VI, § 603(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/1767"},"text":"135 Stat. 1767","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida9d0f3c0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida9d0f3c1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida9d0f3c2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 452” for “section 474”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2013—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/s1076/a/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, § 1076(a)(9)","children":[],"tail":", made technical amendment to directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/81/s631/f/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–81, § 631(f)(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":". See 2011 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/81/s631/f/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–81, § 631(f)(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/s1076/a/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, § 1076(a)(9)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “474” for “404”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/364"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–364","children":[],"tail":" substituted “card” for “care”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/s1009/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, § 1009(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “The Secretary of Defense shall require” for “The Secretary of Defense may require”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2), (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/s1009/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, § 1009(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), added par. (2) and redesignated former par. (2) as (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (d) to (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/s1009/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, § 1009(b)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(1), added subsecs. (d) and (e) and redesignated former subsecs. (d) and (e) as (f) and (g), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida9d0f3c3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida9d0f3c4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2013 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/dA/tX/s1076/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, div. A, title X, § 1076(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1947"},"text":"126 Stat. 1947","children":[],"tail":", provided that the amendment made by section 1076(a)(9) is effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 2011","children":[],"tail":", and as if included in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/81"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–81","children":[],"tail":" as enacted."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"ida9d0f3c5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of authorities, functions, personnel, and assets of the Coast Guard, including the authorities and functions of the Secretary of Transportation relating thereto, to the Department of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see sections 468(b), 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":"section 542 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
